long-range picture. But look what they've got 
already. That's right. Incredible. One of the

24:32.240 --> 24:37.885
problems of the woodlands, I've addressed it a 
number of times, and I keep working on things over

24:32.240 --> 24:37.885
the years. If I agitate enough, ultimately 
somebody does something about it, because they

24:38.606 --> 24:44.231
get tired of hearing me talk about it. When you 
drive into the woodlands, you don't see the

24:44.751 --> 24:49.135
woodlands. You start on the expressway drive in, 
and you say, what the hell is this? It's a lot of

24:52.799 --> 24:53.519
trees. And you see there's a name identification. 
And you say, well, do I want to see Grogan's Mill or

24:58.384 --> 25:00.766
whatever it is? I don't know what it is. Where's the 
pavilion? How do I find it? And all that stuff. So

25:04.954 --> 25:10.663
I've been pushing for kind of a map, a picture map, 
like Life magazine. You open it up, and there'd be a

25:10.683 --> 25:18.596
corollary number on a post, which is number one, 
and the map shows you what's behind the tree. Yeah,

25:18.616 --> 25:19.657
a walking tour. A walking tour of the place. See, 
now, they've gone so far as they're doing a picture

25:21.080 --> 25:24.365
book now. But that isn't what I have in mind. Maybe 
the picture book will suffice. People can get

25:28.131 --> 25:28.892
around. But I want a numbered walking tour or auto 
tour of this place. When you're able to look at it,

25:35.192 --> 25:41.538
if you're just to cut off the, go through the top and 
see this place, it's incredible what's here. But I

25:42.859 --> 25:45.921
see the gorgeous homes here that people are able to 
get. Of course, it's a double-edged sword, too.

25:47.263 --> 25:56.711
One of the things that I sense some of the 
residents, you know, we were talking earlier

25:47.263 --> 25:56.711
about whether the local associations will pick up 
the gauntlet and continue. I see them as actually,

25:56.771 --> 25:59.233
in some ways, jealous of the good things about the 
Woodlands, maybe even the Woodlands Corporation

25:59.568 --> 26:06.816
has been. Because they've really bought into the 
ideas here. That's why they're here. But I've

26:11.141 --> 26:16.527
lived here since 73 and have driven down to Houston 
all the time. And frankly, the Woodlands, as you

26:16.607 --> 26:22.233
said, was to me a wall of trees on the right side of 
I-45 as you drove down. And it had no meaning

26:23.154 --> 26:24.816
whatsoever. But at the same token, were I living 
here, You know, there's some mixed feelings

26:30.753 --> 26:44.695
about, do I want a walking tour where individuals, 
you know, from elsewhere, you know, where the

26:30.753 --> 26:44.695
woodlands becomes a tourist kind of event for its 
continued growth. You live here now? No. Oh, you

26:46.337 --> 26:47.279
did live here? No. College Station. College 
Station is where I'm from. I live up here in

26:50.043 --> 26:51.485
Coliseum. Well, you know, it's the same problem 
we're dealing with, the universities versus

26:51.966 --> 26:55.832
Harkin. If the people who live in the woodlands 
realize that if this community grows, they'll get

26:56.015 --> 27:05.067
more things here, they'll get that movie theater 
right in here. They'll get the shopping centers

27:05.247 --> 27:07.170
and all that. So you have to take a long view of the 
welfare. And my feeling is that if more people came

27:11.296 --> 27:16.703
and saw this place, more people would want to come 
and live here. It's that simple. I've always, I

27:18.445 --> 27:22.731
like the title, I guess, The Machine in the Garden. 
And I see that as one of the possible tensions of the

27:23.099 --> 27:26.563
future in the woodlands. Too much development. Of 
course, the kind of development they're trying to

27:29.426 --> 27:35.012
do is trying to tone that down a little bit. Too much 
business, if you will, that might disturb the

27:35.192 --> 27:43.521
garden aspects of the woodlands as one of the 
futures. They don't want any infringement on

27:43.541 --> 27:45.884
their privacy. No, that's right. Can you have it 
both? Can you have progress and can you have

27:47.826 --> 27:49.528
progress? Look, I live in condominiums in Chicago 
and in Palm Springs. And there's some things I have

27:56.221 --> 28:00.305
to do as kind of a social enterprise. I have to do as 
an owner of a condominium apartment or home. I've

28:05.010 --> 28:06.131
got to live with my neighbors. I don't like the fact 
that the pool is filled with children on holidays.

28:11.136 --> 28:15.060
I don't like the fact the neighbor across the 
street has a dog that barks once in a while. or

28:15.513 --> 28:23.184
there's another neighbor who's visited by a 
relative with a recreational vehicle, and it's

28:15.513 --> 28:23.184
parked in the street, some things I don't like. If 
they're against the condominium rules, I protest

28:24.106 --> 28:28.152
it and get it stopped. But if it's just a violation 
of what I consider my privacy, I either have to live

28:28.893 --> 28:34.181
with it or I have to move. And the same thing here. If 
you're living here, if you want the place to offer

28:36.284 --> 28:41.892
you all the good things you want in life, You have to 
participate in the growth of this community and

28:42.665 --> 28:48.150
the recognition of this community. I think that's 
the key. And apparently the Woodlands has done a

28:48.990 --> 28:55.036
good job, I think, of organizing such that there is 
participation. Well, the infrastructure

28:55.056 --> 28:56.297
itself. The infrastructure itself is a 
conservative instrument. It maintains, well,

28:59.420 --> 29:03.003
the natural environment. That's a sacrosanct. 
Yes, sure. In fact, they're moving. Bill

29:08.167 --> 29:11.490
Kendrick, who's responsible for the grounds 
here, One thing to ask myself is, is there, in fact,

29:11.740 --> 29:16.505
a set of rules, regulations? Has the things which 
you have developed been codified? And he says, no,

29:19.048 --> 29:21.051
but we're going to do that. He says, we've arrived 
at the point where we can do that. And I think that

29:24.495 --> 29:37.950
infrastructure is what's going to preserve the 
integrity of the ruins, for want of a better term,

29:24.495 --> 29:37.950
through the stages of growth.

29:39.078 --> 29:44.385
I think it's an exciting project, and it's true to 
its principles. And as long as George stays alive,

29:44.405 --> 29:47.048
it'll be true. He's got a son on the board now, and 
his son probably will carry on those principles

29:47.068 --> 29:54.758
for the years. And George, of course, has always 
maintained control over the corporation, so

29:54.838 --> 30:00.105
nobody can take it away from him. Not from the 
standpoint of preserving his wealth so much, but

30:00.866 --> 30:06.773
preserving his control. You know, we talk about 
proxy fights and all that. Can't do that with

30:09.598 --> 30:11.841
Mitchell Energy, you know. What the hell is he is 
when a guy owns more than 60% of the company? And,

30:16.406 --> 30:23.194
you know, you talk to George about wealth, he never 
is concerned about his own wealth. I've never

30:23.214 --> 30:25.517
heard him talk along those lines. God, I just lost 
$2 million today or something like that. He

30:29.262 --> 30:30.864
doesn't do that like most executives. That's an 
abstraction to him. It's a benchmark when he has to

30:32.886 --> 30:36.270
look at it. What he's mostly concerned is going 
ahead with his dreams. And that includes, of

30:40.760 --> 30:44.224
course, the enormous job. Have you looked at 
Galveston recently, what he's done there? Yeah, I

30:46.767 --> 30:48.228
spent a lot of time there. Yeah. Well, it's 
enormous what they've done. Each year I come down,

30:51.252 --> 30:54.616
there's something new. The restaurant across the 
way, I forget the name of it. God, you can't get in

30:57.920 --> 30:59.281
the place. And that Irish pub, can't get in the 
place. his vision and building, you know,

31:05.056 --> 31:07.899
bringing the Mardi Gras back. Yeah, that worked. 
Yeah, great idea.

